  Sitemap index for mrcglobalpay.com.

  Children are served by the dynamic-feed edge function on Supabase because
  Lovable hosting does not honor public/_redirects for /sitemap-*.xml paths.
  Cross-host children inside a sitemap index are accepted by Google/Bing as
  long as the host of THIS index file (mrcglobalpay.com) is verified in
  Search Console — no need to verify the supabase.co host.

  ── Auto-sync note ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  This static stub mirrors the dynamic index emitted by the edge function at
  https://tjikwxkmsfmyjkssvyoh.supabase.co/functions/v1/dynamic-feed?p=/

  The dynamic endpoint reads sync_engine_state.pairs_count and emits one
  child per 1500 pairs automatically — so it stays in sync as the pair table
  grows. robots.txt also references that dynamic endpoint, so crawlers will
  pick up new batches without any code change required here.

  This static file is kept as a fallback discovery point and contains a
  generous batch range (currently 0–29, covering ~45,000 pairs / ~585k URLs)
  so search engines following https://mrcglobalpay.com/sitemap.xml will see
  every batch even if the edge function is briefly unreachable.
  Extra unused batch URLs (above the live count) simply return 200 with an
  empty <urlset>, which is valid per sitemaps.org.
-->
